<p>I'm trying to code a way to rotate a <code>div</code> on mouse hover and show a different content than before. </p>  <p>An example can be seen here: <a href="http://www.possibile.com" rel="nofollow">www.possibile.com</a></p>  <p>And here is my code for what I'm trying to do: </p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>#container {   width: 500px;   height: 500px;   margin: 0 auto; } .rotate {   width: 200px;   height: 200px;   margin: 150px;   background-color: red;   -webkit-transition: 1s ease-in;   -moz-transition: 1s ease-in;   -o-transition: 1s ease-in;   transition: 1s ease-in; } .rotate:hover {   -webkit-transform: rotateY(180deg);   -moz-transform: rotateY(180deg);   -o-transform: rotateY(180deg);   -ms-transform: rotateY(180deg);   transform: rotateY(180deg); } .rotate:hover &gt; p.front {   display: none; } p.rear {   display: none;   -webkit-transform: rotateY(-180deg);   -moz-transform: rotateY(-180deg);   -o-transform: rotateY(-180deg);   -ms-transform: rotateY(-180deg);   transform: rotateY(-180deg); } .rotate:hover &gt; p.rear {   display: block; }</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;div id="container"&gt;    &lt;div class="rotate"&gt;     &lt;p class="front"&gt;This is a div to rotate.&lt;/p&gt;     &lt;p class="rear"&gt;       This is the div rotated.     &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>  <p><a href="http://jsfiddle.net/wLLLsjLd/1/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/wLLLsjLd/1/</a></p>  <p>The problem with my code is that whenever I hover upon the <code>div</code>, it shows the "rear" p at the beginning of the rotation and not in the end.</p>  <p>Any help?</p>